HEADWORD: Cabriole
<hw>Cab"ri*ole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Cabriolet</er>, and cf. <er>Capriole</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Man.)</fld>
<def>A curvet; a leap. See <er>Capriole</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>cabrioles</qex> which his charger exhibited.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

